---

<footer class="footer">
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <div class="footer-top">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <span class="footer-logo">JV</span>
        <span class="footer-tagline">Backend Isolationist</span>
      </div>

      <div class="footer-links">
        <button class="footer-link" data-modal="terms"
          >Terms of Endurance</button
        >
        <button class="footer-link" data-modal="privacy"
          >Data Avoidance Policy</button
        >
        <button class="footer-link" data-modal="refund"
          >Transactional Regret</button
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer-line"></div>

    <div class="footer-bottom">
      <span class="footer-copy"
        >© 2026 Jaime Villalba. All rights reserved.</span
      >
      <span class="footer-built">Crafted with severe anxiety</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<!-- Policy Modals -->
<div class="modal-overlay" id="modal-overlay">
  <div class="modal">
    <button class="modal-close" aria-label="Close">
      <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
        <path
          d="M5 5l10 10M15 5L5 15"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          stroke-linecap="round"></path>
      </svg>
    </button>

    <div class="modal-content" id="modal-terms">
      <h3>Terms of Endurance</h3>
      <p>
        By accessing this domain, you acknowledge that nothing here is
        guaranteed. This server is sustained entirely by the same volatile
        mixture of espresso and anxiety that I am.<br /><br />1. <strong
          >Uptime:</strong
        > I reserve the right to completely nuke this deployment without warning if
        the repository structure begins to visually displease me or if I experience
        a depressive episode.<br />2. <strong>Usage:</strong> Do not attempt to reverse-engineer
        my code. Not because it is proprietary, but because it is structurally dependent
        on my specific neuroses and will break if exposed to standard logic.<br
        />3. <strong>Expectations:</strong> If you find a bug, keep it to yourself.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="modal-content" id="modal-privacy">
      <h3>Data Avoidance Policy</h3>
      <p>
        I do not want your data. I do not use Google Analytics or tracking
        cookies because the thought of perceiving human traffic in real-time
        induces panic.<br /><br />If you are foolish enough to submit the
        contact form, your exact string literals will be forcefully sanitized
        and stored in a completely isolated, volume-mapped Docker container. I
        will not share this data with third parties because that would require
        speaking to third parties. I will likely never even look at the
        database.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="modal-content" id="modal-refund">
      <h3>Transactional Regret</h3>
      <p>
        I do not actively sell products here, making the concept of a refund
        completely illogical.<br /><br />If you have somehow managed to inject
        money into my infrastructure, you have exploited a vulnerability that
        does not exist. Consider those funds a forced donation to my caffeine
        dependency. I will not reverse the transaction, primarily because
        logging into the payment processor's dashboard requires 2FA and I refuse
        to look for my phone. All interactions are final.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .footer {
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--gutter);
    padding-left: calc(220px + var(--gutter));
    background: var(--surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .footer-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .footer-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .footer-brand {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .footer-logo {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .footer-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .footer-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .footer-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: color var(--duration-fast);
  }

  .footer-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .footer-line {
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .footer-bottom {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .footer-copy,
  .footer-built {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  /* Modal */
  .modal-overlay {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 2000;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out);
  }

  .modal-overlay.active {
    opacity: 1;
    pointer-events: all;
  }

  .modal {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-dim);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 600px;
    width: 100%;
    position: relative;
    transform: translateY(20px);
    transition: transform var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out);
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(200, 63, 109, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .modal-overlay.active .modal {
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  .modal-close {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.25rem;
    right: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: color var(--duration-fast);
  }

  .modal-close:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .modal-content {
    display: none;
  }

  .modal-content.active {
    display: block;
  }

  .modal-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .modal-content p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .footer {
      padding-left: var(--gutter);
    }

    .footer-top {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .footer-bottom {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const overlay = document.getElementById("modal-overlay");
  const contents = document.querySelectorAll(".modal-content");
  const closeBtn = document.querySelector(".modal-close");

  document.querySelectorAll(".footer-link[data-modal]").forEach((btn) => {
    btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const id = btn.getAttribute("data-modal");
      contents.forEach((c) => c.classList.remove("active"));
      document.getElementById(`modal-${id}`)?.classList.add("active");
      overlay?.classList.add("active");
    });
  });

  closeBtn?.addEventListener("click", () =>
    overlay?.classList.remove("active"),
  );
  overlay?.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    if (e.target === overlay) overlay.classList.remove("active");
  });

  document.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if (e.key === "Escape") overlay?.classList.remove("active");
  });
</script>
